      <hedline>
        <hl1>BANKRUPTCIES IN JAPAN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tanikawa, Miki</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Teikoku Databank reports that corporate failures in Japan in first half of its fiscal year left behind liabilities that reached 10.0 trillion yen ($100.9 billion), postwar record; predicts that bankruptcies will also increase in second half (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Corporate failures in Japan in the first half of its fiscal year left behind liabilities that reached 10.9 trillion yen ($100.9 billion), a postwar record, Teikoku Databank reported. In the six months ended Sept. 30, there were 9,473 bankruptcies reported, a 19.6 percent rise from the period a year earlier. Teikoku predicted bankruptcies would also increase in the second half.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa</p>
      </block>
